# JetLag admin UI

This app is **not** built with [Kumo UI](https://kumo-ui.com). The [Kumo Component Registry](https://kumo-ui.com/registry.md) is Cloudflare’s machine-readable catalog (props, variants, examples) for **Kumo** components—use it when intentionally adding or migrating to `@cloudflare/kumo`, via `npx @cloudflare/kumo doc <Component>` or the JSON API.

## Stack in this repo

- **React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS**
- **Radix UI** primitives (`@radix-ui/react-*`) for accessible behavior (switch, dialog, select, etc.)
- **`cn()`** from `@/lib/utils` (clsx + tailwind-merge) for class composition
- **CVA** where variants are needed
- **lucide-react** for icons

## Practices aligned with registry-style systems

1. Prefer **Radix-based wrappers** in `frontend/src/components/ui/` (e.g. `Switch`) over ad-hoc `<button>` toggles so keyboard, ARIA, and focus behavior stay correct.
2. Document **variants** via TypeScript props (`variant?: 'default' | 'violet'`) and `cn()` for track/thumb styles.
3. New interactive controls should have an **`aria-label`** (or associated `<label>`) when the visual context is not enough.
